{
  "texts": [
    "General: Our judges predict human scores using the base judge's rationale and score.",
    "The predictor is a generalized linear model (GLM) (Wolke and Schwetlick, 1988) trained on human scores in the domain.",
    "The judges can be applied to absolute rating prediction, such as regression and classification, or relative preference prediction.",
    "They can also be applied to any base judge because we treat it as a black box.",
    "We show the versatility of our framework by proposing four quantitative judges."
  ]
}